The Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) has congratulated Governor Godwin Obaseki of Edo State on his 64th birthday.
The party in a statement by the National Publicity Secretary, Kola Ologbondiyan, described Governor Obaseki as a courageous leader, very brilliant technocrat, highly resourceful and ingenious administrator, who has continued to exhibit an exceptional commitment towards the unity, stability and development of not only Edo State but the nation at large.
“Our party is proud of the outstanding achievements recorded by Governor Obaseki in the development of Edo State particularly in the critical sectors of infrastructure, education, healthcare, housing, oil and gas, energy, agriculture, industrialization, security and economic empowerment of citizens among others, in line with the manifesto of the PDP,” the statement read in part.
The PDP noted Governor Obaseki’s efforts as the Chairman of the PDP membership e-registration exercise as well as other commitments towards the stability and growth of the  party, in the determination to rescue the nation from the misrule and stranglehold of the APC.
“The PDP congratulates Governor Obaseki on this auspicious occasion and prays to God to continue to bestow him with good health, wisdom and many more years in the service of the nation and humanity,” the statement further read.
